{"id":"shenir","term":"Shenir","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>=Senir, (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 3:9\">Deut. 3:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 4:8\">Cant. 4:8</a>), the name given to Mount Hermon (q.v.) by the Sidonians.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Deuteronomy 3:9","Song of Solomon 4:8"]}